{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "kjva:job.9",
    "translationId": "kjva",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 9,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 9",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 9 in King James Version with Apocrypha."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.9.1",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:1",
      "text": "Then Job answered and said,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.9.2",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:2",
      "text": "I know it is so of a truth: but how should man be just with God?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.9.3",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:3",
      "text": "If he will contend with him, he cannot answer him one of a thousand.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.9.4",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:4",
      "text": "He is wise in heart, and mighty in strength: who hath hardened himself against him, and hath prospered?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.9.5",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:5",
      "text": "Which removeth the mountains, and they know not: which overturneth them in his anger.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.9.6",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:6",
      "text": "Which shaketh the earth out of her place, and the pillars thereof tremble.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.9.7",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:7",
      "text": "Which commandeth the sun, and it riseth not; and sealeth up the stars.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.9.8",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:8",
      "text": "Which alone spreadeth out the heavens, and treadeth upon the waves of the sea.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.9.9",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:9",
      "text": "Which maketh Arcturus, Orion, and Pleiades, and the chambers of the south.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.9.10",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:10",
      "text": "Which doeth great things past finding out; yea, and wonders without number.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.9.11",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:11",
      "text": "Lo, he goeth by me, and I see him not: he passeth on also, but I perceive him not.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.9.12",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:12",
      "text": "Behold, he taketh away, who can hinder him? who will say unto him, What doest thou?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.9.13",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:13",
      "text": "If God will not withdraw his anger, the proud helpers do stoop under him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.9.14",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:14",
      "text": "How much less shall I answer him, and choose out my words to reason with him?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.9.15",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:15",
      "text": "Whom, though I were righteous, yet would I not answer, but I would make supplication to my judge.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.9.16",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:16",
      "text": "If I had called, and he had answered me; yet would I not believe that he had hearkened unto my voice.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.9.17",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:17",
      "text": "For he breaketh me with a tempest, and multiplieth my wounds without cause.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.9.18",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:18",
      "text": "He will not suffer me to take my breath, but filleth me with bitterness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.9.19",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:19",
      "text": "If I speak of strength, lo, he is strong: and if of judgment, who shall set me a time to plead?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.9.20",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:20",
      "text": "If I justify myself, mine own mouth shall condemn me: if I say, I am perfect, it shall also prove me perverse.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.9.21",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:21",
      "text": "Though I were perfect, yet would I not know my soul: I would despise my life.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.9.22",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:22",
      "text": "This is one thing, therefore I said it, He destroyeth the perfect and the wicked.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.9.23",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:23",
      "text": "If the scourge slay suddenly, he will laugh at the trial of the innocent.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.9.24",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:24",
      "text": "The earth is given into the hand of the wicked: he covereth the faces of the judges thereof; if not, where, and who is he?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.9.25",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:25",
      "text": "Now my days are swifter than a post: they flee away, they see no good.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.9.26",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:26",
      "text": "They are passed away as the swift ships: as the eagle that hasteth to the prey.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.9.27",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:27",
      "text": "If I say, I will forget my complaint, I will leave off my heaviness, and comfort myself:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.9.28",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:28",
      "text": "I am afraid of all my sorrows, I know that thou wilt not hold me innocent.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.9.29",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:29",
      "text": "If I be wicked, why then labour I in vain?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.9.30",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:30",
      "text": "If I wash myself with snow water, and make my hands never so clean;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.9.31",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:31",
      "text": "Yet shalt thou plunge me in the ditch, and mine own clothes shall abhor me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.9.32",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:32",
      "text": "For he is not a man, as I am, that I should answer him, and we should come together in judgment.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.9.33",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:33",
      "text": "Neither is there any daysman betwixt us, that might lay his hand upon us both.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.9.34",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:34",
      "text": "Let him take his rod away from me, and let not his fear terrify me:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.9.35",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:35",
      "text": "Then would I speak, and not fear him; but it is not so with me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
